.row
  .text-center
    %h2
      We created the Debezium open source project in early 2016, <br/> and welcome everyone that wants to help us build the best <br/> open source platform for change data capture.
  %br

.row
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-body
      .col-md-2.pull-center
        %i.enormous-icon.icon-edit.circled.pull-center
      .col-md-10
        %h3 "How can I help?"
        %p
          You can contribute in multiple ways: by using Debezium, asking or answering questions, reporting issues, writing documentation, fixing bugs, discussing plans, and developing new features. Set up your local environment, star our 
          <a href="https://github.com/debezium">GitHub repositories</a>, and check out our open issues.
        %a.btn.btn-primary(href="/docs/contribute") Learn how
.row
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-body
      .col-md-2.pull-center
        %i.enormous-icon.icon-comments-alt.circled.pull-center
      .col-md-10
        %h3 "Where can I ask questions?"
        %p
          Our 
          %a(href="/docs") documentation
          is full of useful information, and you might find an answer to your question there. If not, jump into our 
          <a href="https://gitter.im/debezium/user">chat room for users</a> or join our
          <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/debezium">Google Group</a>. Our
          %a(href="https://gitter.im/debezium/dev") developer chat room 
          may be useful if you're interested in the in-depth inner workings of Debezium.
.row
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-body
      .col-md-2.pull-center
        %i.enormous-icon.icon-bullhorn.circled.pull-center
      .col-md-10
        %h3 "I'm using Debezium!"
        %p
          We love to hear how people are using Debezium, so let us know on Twitter <a href="http://twitter.com/debezium">@debezium</a>
          or mention it in the <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/debezium">Google Group</a>.
          Include a link to your project, website, or blog post.
